  "text": "The three benchmarking datasets include movie reviews from IMDB, restaurant reviews from Yelp13 and Yelp14 developed by [CITATION_1] . All datasets are tokenized using the Stanford NLP tool [CITATION_2] . Since postings in social networks by both users and products follow the long tail distribution (Kordumova et al., 2016), we only show the distribution of total number of posts for different products. For example, #p(0-50) means the number of products which have reviews between the size of 0 to 50. We split train/development/test sets at the rate of 8:1:1 following the same setting in [CITATION_3] . The best configuration by the development dataset is used for the test set to obtain the final result.",
